All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class ChooseArtefacts
extends javax.swing.JDialog

ChooseArtefacts dialog allows to select only those artefacts the tester is interested in. To each artefact an so called artefact type must be attached to make sure it is stored in the right data structure. One has the possibility to remove or to add types.

Method Detail

addArtefact

@Action
public void addArtefact()
adds the selected artefact(s) in the list available artefacts to the list of selected artefacts. Only for artefacts which are in the latter list are test datas generated.

removeArtefact

@Action
public void removeArtefact()
removes selected artefact(s) from the list selected artefacts. It is not possible to generate test data for artefacts, which are not in the corresponding list.

accept

@Action
public void accept()
the selected artefacts are passed to the component showing them in the UI. Before this is done, the selection has to be valid, otherwise it's rejected.

A selection is said to be valid, if and only if all artefacts have an artefact type attached.

cancel

@Action
public void cancel()
cancels the this process and closes the frame. No selection or other stuff is going to be saved.

addArtefactType

@Action
public void addArtefactType()
opens a dialog to add a new artefact type.

delArtefactType

@Action
public void delArtefactType()
deletes the current selected artefact type not only from the combo box, but from the model layer. At the model the artefact type and the artefact collection are deleted accordingly.

markAsArtefactType

@Action
public void markAsArtefactType(ArtefactType type)
marks the current selected artefact with the selected element of the combo box. Notice, all artefacts have to be marked with such a type.

Parameters:
type - artefact type to distinguish collections.

setArtefactType

public void setArtefactType(ArtefactType[] types)
with this method the current artefact types are updated. This is done before the dialog is displayed.

Parameters:
types - artefact types

setArtefactType

protected void setArtefactType(java.lang.String name,
                               boolean createDummyFile)
adds a new type of artefact to the list. This is called by an internal input frame.

Parameters:
name - name of a new artefact type
createDummyFile - indicates whether to create dummy files for this kind of artefact type or not.

addElementToAvailableArtefacts

public void addElementToAvailableArtefacts(MetaClass artefact)
adds a artefact to the list of available artefacts.

Parameters:
artefact - a meta class is an enriched object of EMF Ecore's EClass.

resetLists

public void resetLists()
resets the lists in its initial state with no elements within.
